  "english": [
    "<b>And</b> this <b>unattributed</b> opinion in the mishna is <b>in accordance with</b> the opinion of <b>Rabbi Meir. As, if</b> you say that this ruling is in accordance with the opinion of <b>Rabbi Yosei,</b> that cannot be, since he holds that <b>in every place one may rent</b> a house to a gentile, including Eretz Yisrael.",
    "§ The mishna teaches: <b>And in every place, one may not rent</b> a bathhouse to a gentile, as it is called by the name of the owner. The Gemara notes that <b>it is taught</b> in a <i>baraita</i> that <b>Rabban Shimon ben Gamliel says: A person may not rent his bathhouse to a gentile, because it is called by the name of</b> the owner, <b>and this gentile uses it for performing</b> prohibited <b>labor on <i>Shabbatot</i> and on Festivals.</b>",
    "The Gemara asks: It is prohibited to rent one’s bathhouse to a gentile, <b>but</b> with regard <b>to a Samaritan, what</b> is the <i>halakha</i>? It can be inferred from the lack of mention of a Samaritan that it is <b>permitted.</b> The Gemara asks: Why not <b>say</b> that <b>a Samaritan</b> will <b>perform work in</b> the bathhouse <b>during the intermediate days of a Festival?</b> The Gemara answers: <b>During the intermediate days of a Festival we too perform work</b> and heat bathhouses.",
    "The Gemara further infers: It is prohibited to rent one’s bathhouse to a gentile; <b>but</b> with regard to renting <b>one’s field to a gentile, what</b> is the <i>halakha</i>? Evidently, it is <b>permitted. What is the reason</b> for this? People know that a gentile <b>sharecropper works for his tenancy,</b> not for the Jewish owner. The Gemara asks: But if so, in the case of <b>a bathhouse as well,</b> why not <b>say</b> that the gentile <b>sharecropper works for his tenancy,</b> and therefore a Jew should be permitted to rent them to gentiles. The Gemara answers: <b>People do not</b> usually <b>make</b> this type of arrangement whereby a second party works as <b>a sharecropper of a bathhouse.</b> Consequently, it will be assumed that the gentile is a hired worker who is working for the Jew.",
    "The Gemara cites a similar discussion. <b>It is taught</b> in a <i>baraita</i> that <b>Rabbi Shimon ben Elazar says: A person may not rent his field to a Samaritan, since it is called by the name of</b> the owner <b>and this Samaritan</b> will <b>perform work in it during the intermediate days of a Festival.</b> The Gemara infers: It is prohibited to rent one’s field to a Samaritan, <b>but</b> with regard to <b>a gentile, what</b> is the <i>halakha</i>? Evidently, it is <b>permitted, as we say</b> that the gentile <b>sharecropper works for his tenancy</b> and not for the Jewish owner. The Gemara asks: <b>If that is so,</b> in the case of <b>a Samaritan as well,</b> why not <b>say</b> that the <b>sharecropper works for his tenancy?</b>"
  ],
  "gemara": [
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "<span class=\"sentence\" id=\"0\" type=\"start\">&star;</span>וּסְתָמָא <span class=\"name-reference-marker name-reference-tanna\" data-sage-type=\"tanna\" title=\"Rabbi Meir, fifth-generation Tanna\" data-authority-id=\"2068\" data-full-name=\"Rabbi Meir\" data-name-he=\"רבי מאיר\">כְּרַבִּי מֵאִיר</span>, דְּאִי <span class=\"name-reference-marker name-reference-tanna\" data-sage-type=\"tanna\" title=\"Rabbi Yosei, fifth-generation Tanna\" data-authority-id=\"1657\" data-full-name=\"Rabbi Yosei\" data-name-he=\"רבי יוסי בן חלפתא\">רַבִּי יוֹסֵי</span>, בְּכׇל",
      "segment_ids": [
        0
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "דּוּכְתָּא מוֹגְרִי.<span class=\"sugya-marker sugya-marker-vilna-piska\" data-sugya-kind=\"vilna-piska\" data-sugya-id=\"87\" data-raw-symbol=\"׃\">׃</span> <span class=\"sugya-marker sugya-marker-steinsaltz\" data-sugya-kind=\"steinsaltz\" data-sugya-id=\"58\" data-sentence-id=\"1\">§</span> <span class=\"sentence\" id=\"1\" type=\"start\">&star;</span>וּבְכׇל מָקוֹם לֹא יִשְׂכּוֹר וְכוּ׳.<span class=\"sugya-marker sugya-marker-vilna-piska\" data-sugya-kind=\"vilna-piska\" data-sugya-id=\"88\" data-raw-symbol=\"׃\">׃</span>",
      "segment_ids": [
        1
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "תַּנְיָא: <span class=\"name-reference-marker name-reference-tanna\" data-sage-type=\"tanna\" title=\"Rabban Shimon ben Gamliel II, fifth-generation Tanna\" data-authority-id=\"2852\" data-full-name=\"Rabban Shimon ben Gamliel II\" data-name-he=\"רבן שמעון בן גמליאל\">רַבָּן שִׁמְעוֹן בֶּן גַּמְלִיאֵל</span> אוֹמֵר: לֹא",
      "segment_ids": [
        1
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "יִשְׂכּוֹר אָדָם מֶרְחָצוֹ לְגוֹי, מִפְּנֵי",
      "segment_ids": [
        1
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "שֶׁנִּקְרָא עַל שְׁמוֹ, וְגוֹי זֶה עוֹשֶׂה",
      "segment_ids": [
        1
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "בּוֹ מְלָאכָה בְּשַׁבָּתוֹת וּבְיָמִים טוֹבִים. <span class=\"sentence\" id=\"2\" type=\"start\">&star;</span>אֲבָל",
      "segment_ids": [
        2
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "לְכוּתִי, מַאי? שְׁרֵי. כּוּתִי אֵימַר עָבֵיד בֵּיהּ",
      "segment_ids": [
        2
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "מְלָאכָה בְּחוּלּוֹ שֶׁל מוֹעֵד! בְּחוּלּוֹ שֶׁל מוֹעֵד",
      "segment_ids": [
        2
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "אֲנַן נָמֵי עָבְדִינַן. <span class=\"sentence\" id=\"3\" type=\"start\">&star;</span>אֲבָל שָׂדֵהוּ לְגוֹי,",
      "segment_ids": [
        3
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "מַאי? שְׁרֵי. מַאי טַעְמָא? אֲרִיסָא אֲרִיסוּתֵיהּ",
      "segment_ids": [
        3
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "קָעָבֵיד. מֶרְחָץ נָמֵי אָמְרִי: אֲרִיסָא אֲרִיסוּתֵיהּ",
      "segment_ids": [
        3
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "קָעָבֵיד? אֲרִיסָא דְּמֶרְחָץ לָא עָבְדִי אַנְשֵׁי.",
      "segment_ids": [
        3
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "655px",
      "text": "<span class=\"sentence\" id=\"4\" type=\"start\">&star;</span>תַּנְיָא, <span class=\"name-reference-marker name-reference-tanna\" data-sage-type=\"tanna\" title=\"Rabbi Yishmael ben Elazar, sixth-generation Tanna\" data-authority-id=\"2846\" data-full-name=\"Rabbi Yishmael ben Elazar\" data-name-he=\"רבי שמעון בן אלעזר\">רַבִּי שִׁמְעוֹן בֶּן אֶלְעָזָר</span> אוֹמֵר: לֹא יַשְׂכִּיר אָדָם שָׂדֵהוּ לְכוּתִי, מִפְּנֵי שֶׁנִּקְרֵאת",
      "segment_ids": [
        4
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "655px",
      "text": "עַל שְׁמוֹ, וְכוּתִי זֶה עוֹשֶׂה בּוֹ מְלָאכָה בְּחוּלּוֹ שֶׁל מוֹעֵד. אֲבָל גּוֹי מַאי? שְׁרֵי,",
      "segment_ids": [
        4
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "655px",
      "text": "דְּאָמְרִי: אֲרִיסָא אֲרִיסוּתֵיהּ עָבֵיד. אִי הָכִי, כּוּתִי נָמֵי אָמְרִי: אֲרִיסָא אֲרִיסוּתֵיהּ עָבֵיד!",
      "segment_ids": [
        4
      ]
    }
  ],
  "rashi": [
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "",
      "text": "<b>וּסְתָמָא <span class=\"dh-divergent\">כר&quot;מ</span></b> דאמר בא\"י אין",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Avodah Zarah 21b:1:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        0
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "",
      "text": "משכירין: <b>כּוּתִי.</b> לא עביד מלאכה",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Avodah Zarah 21b:3:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        1
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "",
      "text": "בשבת אבל בחולו של מועד עביד",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Avodah Zarah 21b:3:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        1
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "",
      "text": "דלמדרש סופרים לא חיישי: <b>בְּחוּלּוֹ</b>",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Avodah Zarah 21b:3:2",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        1
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "",
      "text": "<b>שֶׁל מוֹעֵד</b> לדידן נמי שרי",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Avodah Zarah 21b:3:2",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        1
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "",
      "text": "להחם מרחצאות: <b>אֲבָל שָׂדֵהוּ <span class=\"dh-divergent\">לעובד</span></b>",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Avodah Zarah 21b:4:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        2
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "",
      "text": "<b><span class=\"dh-divergent\">כוכבים</span> שְׁרֵי.</b> להשכיר היכא דליכא",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Avodah Zarah 21b:4:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        2
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "",
      "text": "למיחש לחניית קרקע כגון בח\"ל ואע\"פ",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Avodah Zarah 21b:4:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        2
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "",
      "text": "שנקראת על שמו לא חשדי ליה דליהוי",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Avodah Zarah 21b:4:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        2
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "",
      "text": "עובד כוכבים שלוחו אלא אמרי",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Avodah Zarah 21b:4:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        2
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "",
      "text": "אריסא הוא וקיבלה עליו למחצה",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Avodah Zarah 21b:4:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        2
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "",
      "text": "לשליש ולרביע ועליו מוטל לעשות:",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Avodah Zarah 21b:4:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        2
      ]
    }
  ],
